CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 27, 1955, pg. 12, reads: "Staunch Friend - Among the many friends and benefactors, who have helped Catherine Wallace in her struggle to reach the concert heights, is Mrs. Julie Moreland, left, a loyal and hardworking member of Central Baptist Church. As always, she has been ready to head up benefits to assist the promising young coloratura. She and Catherine are discussing details for the benefit concert, which will be given by the Cornell E. Talley Gospel Chorus at the church Aug. 26. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Julie Moreland and singer Catherine Wallace seated behind table in Central Baptist Church
